"PB-435-M02G-20" and "2012-6-25" is silkscreened :on the board in the FCC photos. The ''[[Realtek]]'' ADSL SoC may be RTL8676.
The FCC EUT's label shows the device w/ a 08:10:77 OUI :('''netis''''s standard format seems to be 08:10:7x) - it's full MAC appears to be 08:10:77:38:D8:10 / 08:10:77:38:D9:10.
==Probable included PSU(s)== *The FCC docs show the device with a 12V, 1A power supply :('''DongGuan tenpao Power CO., LTD''' NT12V1AUL).
*'''netis''''s datasheet specifies the power supply as 5V, 2A.
